'INPUT LINE' IS AN INPUT SUBROUTINETHATCONFINES THE CURSOR TO ASPECIFIED AREA;DENOTED BY UNDERLINECHARACTERS. ANY PRINTABLE CHARACTERIS ACCEPTED; AND THERETURN KEY CAN BE ENTERED AT ANYPOINT IN THE INPUT; NOT JUST AT THEEND OF THEINPUT.TO USE IT; SET M TO THE INPUTLENGTH. WHEN IT RETURNS; THE INPUTWILL BE STORED IN I$.